    "message_1": "Consider the following function: \n\nf(x) = x^3 - 2x^2 + 3x - 4 \n\na) Use the forward difference formula to approximate f'(2) with a step size of h=0.1. \nb) Use the central difference formula to approximate f''(4) with a step size of h=0.05. \nc) Use the trapezoidal rule to approximate the definite integral of f(x) from x=0 to x=2 with a step size of h=0.25.",
    "message_2": "a) To approximate f'(2) using the forward difference formula, we have:\n\nf'(x) ≈ (f(x + h) - f(x)) / h\n\nLet x = 2 and h = 0.1:\n\nf'(2) ≈ (f(2.1) - f(2)) / 0.1\n\nFirst, we need to find f(2) and f(2.1):\n\nf(2) = (2)^3 - 2(2)^2 + 3(2) - 4 = 8 - 8 + 6 - 4 = 2\nf(2.1) = (2.1)^3 - 2(2.1)^2 + 3(2.1) - 4 ≈ 9.261 - 8.82 + 6.3 - 4 ≈ 2.741\n\nNow, we can find the approximation of f'(2):\n\nf'(2) ≈ (2.741 - 2) / 0.1 ≈ 7.41\n\nb) To approximate f''(4) using the central difference formula, we have:\n\nf''(x) ≈ (f(x + h) - 2f(x) + f(x - h)) / h^2\n\nLet x = 4 and h = 0.05:\n\nf''(4) ≈ (f(4.05) - 2f(4) + f(3.95)) / (0.05)^2\n\nFirst, we need to find f(4), f(4.05), and f(3.95):\n\nf(4) = (4)^3 - 2(4)^2 + 3(4) - 4 = 64 - 32 + 12 - 4 = 40\nf(4.05) ≈ (4.05)^3 - 2(4.05)^2 + 3(4.05) - 4 ≈ 66.120375 - 32.8102 + 12.15 - 4 ≈ 41.460175\nf(3.95) ≈ (3.95)^3 - 2(3.95)^2 + 3(3.95) - 4 ≈ 61.920875 - 31.2402 + 11.85 - 4 ≈ 38.530675\n\nNow, we can find the approximation of f''(4):\n\nf''(4) ≈ (41.460175 - 2(40) + 38.530675) / (0.05)^2 ≈ 58.01\n\nc) To approximate the definite integral of f(x) from x=0 to x=2 using the trapezoidal rule with a step size of h=0.25, we have:\n\n∫f(x)dx ≈ (h/2) * (f(x0) + 2f(x1) + 2f(x2) + ... + 2f(xn-1) + f(xn))\n\nLet x0 = 0, x1 = 0.25, x2 = 0.5, x3 = 0.75, x4 = 1, x5 = 1.25, x6 = 1.5, x7 = 1.75, and x8 = 2:\n\nf(0) = 0^3 - 2(0)^2 + 3(0) - 4 = -4\nf(0.25) ≈ -3.515625\nf(0.5) = -2\nf(0.75) ≈ -0.421875\nf(1) = -1\nf(1.25) ≈ 0.984375\nf(1.5) = 3\nf(1.75) ≈ 5.078125\nf(2) = 2\n\nNow, we can find the approximation of the definite integral:\n\n∫f(x)dx ≈ (0.25/2) * (-4 + 2(-3.515625) + 2(-2) + 2(-0.421875) - 2 + 2(0.984375) + 2(3) + 2(5.078125) + 2) ≈ -1.25"
